#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code try karta hai ki k cards me kitne front se aur kitne back se lene chahiye
taaki maximum sum mile.

1. Pehle k cards ka sum left side se nikaal liya gaya hai.
   Isse ek initial answer mil gaya.
2. Ab step by step:
   - left side se ek card hata rahe hain
   - right side se ek card add kar rahe hain
3. Har step par check karte hain ki
   current combination ka sum pehle wale max se bada hai ya nahi.
4. Is tarah saare possible combinations cover ho jaate hain:
   - k from left, 0 from right
   - k-1 from left, 1 from right
   - k-2 from left, 2 from right
   - ...
   - 0 from left, k from right

Main idea:
Exact k cards lene hain sirf ends se,
to bas front/back split ke saare possibilities check kar lo.

Time Complexity: O(k)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int maxScore(int[] cardPoints, int k) {
        int lSum = 0;
        int rSum = 0;
        int maxSum = 0;
        int n = cardPoints.length;

        for(int i=0; i<=k-1; i++){
            lSum += cardPoints[i];
        }
        maxSum = lSum;

        //now front se ek hatao aur back se add krte rho
        int rIdx = n-1;
        for(int i=k-1; i>=0; i--){
            lSum -= cardPoints[i];
            rSum += cardPoints[rIdx];
            maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, lSum + rSum);
            rIdx = rIdx - 1;
        }

        return maxSum;
    }
}
